<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="260" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW 1939/2088</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                            (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-30">December 30, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Referring to the last paragraph, numbered 4, of the British memorandum
                        containing the text of telegram dated December 25 from Mr. Eden, hereto
                            attached,<note n="21" xml:id="d260fn21">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                        </note> I informed Mr. Michael Wright, Secretary<note n="22" xml:id="d260fn22">First Secretary.</note> of the British Embassy, that
                        this Government was fully in accord with the proposed reply to be made by
                        the British Government to the reported approach from German sources.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">James Clement Dunn</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>